 ### Failure modes
 
+These describe per-tick semantics. Each fire of the
+`reckoner.tick` relay applies the rules below before, during, and
+after the scheduler call:
+
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started` (no active scheduler resolved)   | Throws fail-loud (`[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved`). Production never trips this; tests rely on the deterministic throw. |
+| Empty candidate set                                                | Early-return; no scheduler call, no rows, no errors. |
+| Dedupe match on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)`                 | The writ is filtered out before `SchedulerInput` is built — the scheduler never sees a writ whose decision the row writer would silently discard. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] tick:` prefix; the entire tick is skipped (no rows for any writ in this fire). |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped. |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. The other in-scope decisions still apply. |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped (no decision is applied for any writ in this fire). |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored; sibling in-scope decisions still apply. |
 
